1
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:42,774
<i>[Man Narrating]</i>
<i>Let me tell you about my day so far.</i>

2
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:44,776
<i>Coffee in Paris,</i>
<i>surfed the Maldives...</i>

3
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:47,278
<i>took a little nap</i>
<i>on Mount Kilimanjaro.</i>

4
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:50,281
<i>Oh, yeah, and I got digits</i>
<i>from this Polish chick in Rio.</i>

5
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:52,283
<i>And then I jumped back...</i>

6
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:54,127
<i>for the final quarter
of the N.B.A. finals...</i>

7
00:00:54,227 --> 00:00:55,013
<i>courtside, of course.</i>

8
00:00:55,121 --> 00:00:57,021
<i>And all that was before lunch.</i>

9
00:00:57,123 --> 00:00:59,023
<i>I could go on,</i>
<i>but all I'm saying is...</i>

10
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:01,093
<i>I'm standing on top of the world.</i>

11
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,464
The lighter terrain here...

12
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:09,296
<i>[Man Narrating]</i>
<i>It wasn't always like this.</i>

13
00:01:09,402 --> 00:01:13,429
<i>Once I was a normal person,</i>
<i>a chump just like you.</i>

14
00:01:16,209 --> 00:01:18,677
- Hey, Millie.
- Oh, hey, David.

15
00:01:22,315 --> 00:01:24,340
You got a lot of cities there.

16
00:01:24,451 --> 00:01:27,420
<i>Well, if you're gonna have a dream,</i>
<i>might as well dream big, right?</i>

17
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:29,420
<i>- Right.</i>
<i>- [Bell Ringing]</i>

18
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:31,422
See you later.

19
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:43,100
Hey, Millie.

20
00:01:45,038 --> 00:01:47,165
Give me a sec.
Hey.

21
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:51,935
I wanted to give you this.

22
00:01:52,035 --> 00:01:54,205
I picked it up at a
yard sale in Plymouth.

23
00:01:54,314 --> 00:01:56,282
I-I thought you'd really like it.

24
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:04,685
It's a little dinged up
and it's missing a few steps, but...

25
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:08,589
I love it.

26
00:02:08,695 --> 00:02:11,220
- You do?
- I do.

27
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:12,855
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>Holy crap, Rice Bowl!</i>

28
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:15,799
- Mark.
- Hey, what's this?

29
00:02:15,902 --> 00:02:17,802
- Christmas come early?
- Mark, stop it.

30
00:02:17,904 --> 00:02:20,031
- Mark, give it back to her.
<i>- Holy crap!</i>

31
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:23,132
Look what David got Millie!
You guys like the Eiffel Tower?

32
00:02:23,243 --> 00:02:25,151
Wow, if you shake this
thing hard enough,

33
00:02:25,251 --> 00:02:26,872
you can hear the Eiffel Tower move.

34
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:30,279
- Hey, who wants to give it a shake?
- Okay, that's enough!

35
00:02:30,383 --> 00:02:32,749
- Stop it. Just give it back.
- All right.

36
00:02:32,852 --> 00:02:34,820
Okay, I'm sorry.
Here.

37
00:02:39,359 --> 00:02:41,259
<i>[Students Laughing,</i>
<i>Chattering]</i>

38
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:44,592
Sorry, buddy.
Guess I don't know my own strength.

39
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:49,731
- I can't believe you're such a jerk!
- I was just playing around.

40
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:50,674
<i>- It wasn't funny.</i>

41
00:02:50,774 --> 00:02:52,896
[Chuckles] They thought
it was pretty funny.

42
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:56,032
<i>[Millie]</i>
<i>David?</i>

43
00:02:56,142 --> 00:02:58,838
David, don't go out there.
It's not safe.

44
00:02:58,945 --> 00:03:00,845
David, just forget about it.

45
00:03:00,947 --> 00:03:03,279
Come on, Rice Bowl!
Don't be stupid!

46
00:03:03,383 --> 00:03:06,716
David, come back. Come on.
Just let it go. It's okay!

47
00:03:07,921 --> 00:03:11,220
<i>Stop! It's not worth it.</i>
<i>Just come back. Please?</i>

48
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,121
Come on, David!

49
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:19,530
<i>[Millie]</i>
<i>Be careful. Come on.</i>

50
00:03:19,632 --> 00:03:21,964
- All good. See?
<i>- [Mark] Great. Now come back.</i>

51
00:03:23,069 --> 00:03:24,900
<i>[Millie Screams]</i>

52
00:03:25,004 --> 00:03:27,871
- David!
- Millie, don't go out there!

53
00:03:27,974 --> 00:03:32,377
<i>[Millie, Muffled]</i>
<i>David! David! Somebody...</i>

54
00:03:32,478 --> 00:03:35,879
- [Groaning, Muffled]
<i>- [Millie] Oh, my God!</i>

55
00:03:35,982 --> 00:03:39,042
- David... Get help!
- Millie, get back here!

56
00:03:39,152 --> 00:03:42,019
<i>[Millie]</i>
<i>Please help! David!</i>

57
00:03:42,121 --> 00:03:44,851
<i>- Call 911! David!</i>
- You can't help him!

58
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:46,687
<i>- Millie, stop, stop, stop!</i>
<i>- David!</i>

59
00:03:46,793 --> 00:03:48,522
<i>[Sirens Wailing]</i>

60
00:03:48,628 --> 00:03:50,755
[Groaning]

61
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:57,199
[Spitting, Coughing]

62
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:03,041
<i>[Coughing Continues]</i>

63
00:04:10,049 --> 00:04:10,854
<i>[David Narrating]</i>

64
00:04:10,954 --> 00:04:13,018
<i>And that's how it
happened the first time.</i>

65
00:04:13,119 --> 00:04:15,357
<i>One second I'm a goner,
and the next thing</i>

66
00:04:15,457 --> 00:04:17,749
<i>I know I'm at the Ann
Arbor Public Library.</i>

67
00:04:31,170 --> 00:04:33,365
<i>Home, sweet home.</i>

68
00:04:35,942 --> 00:04:38,069
<i>Mom left when I was five.</i>

69
00:04:38,177 --> 00:04:42,136
<i>As for Dad, well, let's just say</i>
<i>he wasn't much of one.</i>

70
00:04:46,152 --> 00:04:49,553
<i>You're late.</i>
<i>Supper's cold.</i>

71
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:53,057
[Men On TV,
Indistinct]

72
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:55,821
<i>Where you been, anyway?</i>

73
00:04:55,928 --> 00:04:57,919
[Squishing, Squeaking]

74
00:04:58,031 --> 00:05:00,932
You know, when I ask a question,
I expect an answer. Okay?

75
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:03,195
Hey, hey, hey.
What happened to you?

76
00:05:05,371 --> 00:05:07,271
Just kids at school.

77
00:05:07,373 --> 00:05:12,106
Hey, David, get back down here,
get a mop and clean this crap up!

78
00:05:12,211 --> 00:05:14,111
<i>David!</i>

79
00:05:14,213 --> 00:05:16,306
<i>Don't make me come up there!</i>

80
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,907
<i>David?</i>
<i>Make the right choice!</i>

81
00:05:19,018 --> 00:05:22,112
<i>- [Door Rattling]</i>
- David! David.

82
00:05:22,221 --> 00:05:24,280
Open the door.

83
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:49,377
Did I just teleport?

84
00:05:52,318 --> 00:05:54,286
Great.

85
00:05:55,488 --> 00:05:57,820
I teleported to the library.

86
00:06:24,817 --> 00:06:27,718
<i>[Men Conversing,</i>
<i>Indistinct]</i>

87
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:30,471
<i>Look... No, no, no.
I'm not going anywhere.</i>

88
00:06:30,571 --> 00:06:32,154
<i>I don't care what you say.</i>

89
00:06:32,258 --> 00:06:34,954
<i>[David Narrating]</i>
<i>And that's when it occurred to me.</i>

90
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:38,519
<i>This thing that just happened,</i>
<i>it could set me free.</i>

91
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:50,409
<i>And if she could run away,</i>
<i>so could I.</i>

92
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:56,382
You're okay.

93
00:07:04,657 --> 00:07:06,625
<i>[Tap On Window]</i>

94
00:07:07,994 --> 00:07:10,258
<i>[Tap On Window]</i>

95
00:07:16,969 --> 00:07:19,233
[Chain Squeaking]

96
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,548
<i>[Squeaking Continues]</i>

97
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:36,789
[Gasps]

98
00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:42,818
<i>[David Narrating]</i>
<i>I wanted to tell her everything.</i>

99
00:07:42,929 --> 00:07:44,897
David?

100
00:07:46,332 --> 00:07:48,232
David?

101
00:07:48,334 --> 00:07:49,041
<i>[David Narrating]</i>

102
00:07:49,141 --> 00:07:50,962
<i>I mean, who would have
believed me anyway?</i>

103
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:53,002
<i>[Millie]</i>
<i>David!</i>

104
00:07:53,105 --> 00:07:56,074
<i>[David Narrating]</i>
<i>I figured it was time to move on.</i>

105
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:24,203
Uh, I'd like a room.

106
00:08:24,303 --> 00:08:27,636
You're not gonna be any trouble,
are you? No weird stuff?

107
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:31,437
Nope.
No weird stuff.

108
00:08:38,284 --> 00:08:40,718
<i>[Dog Barking, Growling]</i>

109
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:46,458
[Chuckles]

110
00:08:50,463 --> 00:08:52,363
<i>[David Narrating]</i>
<i>And so there I was.</i>

111
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:56,128
<i>I had a million questions,</i>
<i>like how does this thing work?</i>

112
00:08:56,235 --> 00:08:58,203
<i>How do I control it?</i>

113
00:09:13,452 --> 00:09:15,420
[Groans]

114
00:09:45,318 --> 00:09:47,377
Been there.

115
00:09:47,486 --> 00:09:50,455
<i>[David] Mommy, you can see</i>
<i>the ocean and everything!</i>

116
00:09:50,556 --> 00:09:53,116
If we're lucky,
maybe we'll see King Kong.

117
00:09:53,225 --> 00:09:55,125
- Really?
- [Laughs]

118
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:58,663
- You got me?
- Oh, I got you. I'm not letting you go.

119
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:06,767
<i>[Rumbling]</i>

120
00:10:23,422 --> 00:10:25,686
<i>[David Narrating]</i>
<i>I was 15.</i>

121
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:29,318
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>What would you <i>have done? </i></i>

122
00:10:29,428 --> 00:10:32,397
<i>I figured I'd pay it back someday.</i>

123
00:10:38,371 --> 00:10:40,339
Is there a bathroom for customers?

124
00:10:52,451 --> 00:10:54,681
Hey.
It's this way.

125
00:10:54,787 --> 00:10:56,755
Yeah.

126
00:10:57,957 --> 00:10:59,857
Make it quick.

127
00:10:59,959 --> 00:11:02,086
No problem.
Thanks.

128
00:11:44,937 --> 00:11:46,996
I'm gonna need a bigger bag.

129
00:11:49,442 --> 00:11:52,605
<i># [Rock]</i>

130
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:57,376
<i># Hey, I'm not all alone #</i>

131
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:04,513
<i># Hey, you can tag along #</i>

132
00:12:05,624 --> 00:12:07,990
<i># 'Cause I have</i>
<i>done it before #</i>

133
00:12:08,094 --> 00:12:09,994
<i># And I can do it some more #</i>

134
00:12:10,096 --> 00:12:11,825
<i># I got my eye on the score #</i>

135
00:12:11,931 --> 00:12:14,593
<i># I'm gonna crash through the door</i>
<i>It's too late #</i>

136
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:16,668
Holy shit.

137
00:12:16,769 --> 00:12:18,737
Whoo!

138
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:21,872
<i># [Rock Continues]</i>

139
00:12:21,974 --> 00:12:23,874
- Hey!
<i>- # [Continues]</i>

140
00:12:23,976 --> 00:12:25,413
I said no weird stuff.

141
00:12:25,513 --> 00:12:28,436
Let's go... two days'
rent. You owe me rent.

142
00:12:28,547 --> 00:12:30,447
<i>- [Knocks]</i>
- Hello? Hello?

143
00:12:30,549 --> 00:12:32,517
<i>[Paper Slides]</i>

144
00:12:48,367 --> 00:12:51,268
The police and the F.B.I.
Have already been through here.

145
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:53,895
- Who are you with?
- N.S.A.

146
00:12:54,006 --> 00:12:56,406
<i>They couldn't make</i>
<i>heads or tails of it.</i>

147
00:12:56,509 --> 00:12:59,910
The vault has a time lock,
pressure mounts, steel plates.

148
00:13:00,012 --> 00:13:01,912
- This guy didn't open a door.
- Open a door?

149
00:13:02,014 --> 00:13:04,915
We didn't know we were robbed
until halfway through the day.

150
00:13:05,017 --> 00:13:07,383
I want the security tapes
for the whole month.

151
00:13:07,486 --> 00:13:11,388
And I need the name of everyone who has
a safety deposit box in that vault.

152
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:14,482
That's confidential.
Why do you need those names?

153
00:13:14,593 --> 00:13:17,994
Whoever robbed your vault
has been in it before.

154
00:13:18,097 --> 00:13:21,157
Now, I want those names,
and I want those tapes.

155
00:13:21,267 --> 00:13:23,167
Today.

156
00:13:39,885 --> 00:13:42,615
<i>[David Narrating]</i>
<i>So the story had a happy ending.</i>

157
00:13:42,721 --> 00:13:46,418
<i>Rice Bowl was dead,</i>
<i>but I had never been more alive.</i>

158
00:13:48,027 --> 00:13:49,927
<i>So now I'm living in New York.</i>

159
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:52,429
<i>[Chuckles]</i>
<i>But why settle in one place...</i>

160
00:13:52,531 --> 00:13:54,829
<i>when you can have the whole world?</i>

161
00:13:56,869 --> 00:13:59,337
<i># I was hip to the beat</i>
<i>on city streets #</i>

162
00:13:59,438 --> 00:14:02,566
<i># I saw a signpost tellin'me
to pick my feet...</i>

163
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:04,205
<i>off the ground, y'all #</i>

164
00:14:07,546 --> 00:14:09,104
<i># Said "I think"</i>
<i>to the shrink #</i>

165
00:14:09,215 --> 00:14:11,740
<i># I tell her</i>
<i>well, 'bout my lover #</i>

166
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:15,184
<i># She tell me, "Get a dog</i>
<i>that says bow-wow-wow"#</i>

167
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:20,551
[Announcer]
She floats into the river.

168
00:14:20,659 --> 00:14:24,151
But as you can see, this flood became
more severe about 10 minutes ago.

169
00:14:24,263 --> 00:14:27,391
The question now, Pat, is,
what will happen to these people?

170
00:14:27,499 --> 00:14:29,592
<i>It would take a miracle</i>
<i>to get to them.</i>

171
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:33,399
<i># [Continues]</i>

172
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:55,694
<i># [Fades]</i>

173
00:14:55,794 --> 00:14:57,921
<i>Good afternoon, Mr. Jones.</i>

174
00:14:59,531 --> 00:15:01,761
- How they doin'?
- Down by six at the half.

175
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:04,768
Don't think you'll be
needing that umbrella.

176
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:07,100
You never know.

177
00:15:07,273 --> 00:15:10,140
<i>[Bells Tolling]</i>

178
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:12,210
<i>[Whoosh]</i>

179
00:15:13,812 --> 00:15:16,781
[Tolling Continues]

180
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:23,184
<i>[Rain Pattering]</i>

181
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:28,283
<i>[Bell Chiming]</i>

182
00:15:28,394 --> 00:15:31,363
<i>- # [Rock]</i>
- [People Chattering]

183
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:54,184
<i>- [Man] Watch it!</i>
<i>- [David] You mind if I join you?</i>

184
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:56,914
<i>- [Woman] No.</i>
- What are you drinking?

185
00:15:57,022 --> 00:15:58,751
Gin and tonic.

186
00:15:58,857 --> 00:16:03,191
Uh, Tanqueray and tonic.
Two of'em, please.

187
00:16:06,098 --> 00:16:10,057
So, you live in London?

188
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:12,160
<i># We lay down the law #</i>

189
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:14,796
- Taxi!
<i>- # So what the hell are you here for #</i>

190
00:16:14,907 --> 00:16:17,068
<i># We lay down the law #</i>

191
00:16:17,176 --> 00:16:19,644
<i># So what you need me for #</i>

192
00:16:39,131 --> 00:16:40,598
[Whispers]
Shit.

193
00:16:52,211 --> 00:16:54,179
Dude, this totally sucks.

194
00:16:55,814 --> 00:16:58,715
Hey, I thought this was where the storm
was supposed to hit.

195
00:16:58,817 --> 00:17:01,479
- I heard it hit Fiji.
- Fiji, huh?

196
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:04,351
Yeah. They got,
like, 30-foot swells.

197
00:17:04,456 --> 00:17:06,117
Really?

198
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:14,731
Wh... Whoa!

199
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:17,324
[Yelling]

200
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:55,195
<i>- [Explosions, Gunfire]</i>
<i>- [Men Shouting]</i>

201
00:17:59,278 --> 00:18:02,213
<i>- [Groaning]</i>
<i>- [Explosions, Gunfire Continue]</i>

202
00:18:07,186 --> 00:18:09,279
Let's go.

203
00:18:11,857 --> 00:18:14,451
<i>- [Electricity Crackling]</i>
<i>- [Groaning Continues]</i>

204
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:19,622
<i>¿Por qué?</i>
<i>¿Por qué? Why?</i>

205
00:18:19,731 --> 00:18:23,428
Because you are an abomination.

206
00:18:23,535 --> 00:18:26,436
<i>- [Electricity Crackling]</i>
- [Man Groaning, Screaming]

207
00:18:26,538 --> 00:18:29,632
Only God should have the power...

208
00:18:29,741 --> 00:18:32,505
to be all places at all times.

209
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:38,917
[Grunts]

210
00:18:45,624 --> 00:18:49,025
[Whimpering]

211
00:18:53,332 --> 00:18:55,800
One less of you to worry about.

212
00:18:58,670 --> 00:19:00,865
Cut him down!

213
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:03,601
Let's get the hell out of here.

214
00:19:03,709 --> 00:19:05,904
<i>- [Phone Rings]</i>
- Yeah?

215
00:19:06,011 --> 00:19:08,912
We have a lead on the bank, sir.

216
00:19:09,014 --> 00:19:11,539
I'll be on the next plane.

217
00:19:18,423 --> 00:19:20,323
Hey, Angelo.
How'd they do?

218
00:19:20,425 --> 00:19:22,325
- Not so good.
- Ah.

219
00:19:22,427 --> 00:19:25,148
- Told you you wouldn't
be needing that umbrella.

220
00:19:25,248 --> 00:19:26,386
Yeah. You were right.

221
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:40,410
# [Whistling]

222
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:42,480
# [Stops]

223
00:19:44,383 --> 00:19:46,510
<i>Don't run.</i>

